{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"First-time same-chain borrow bypasses collateral check","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:152","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:157","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:161","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:167"],"claim":"`CoreRouter.borrow` computes `borrowAmount` as `0` when `currentBorrow.borrowIndex == 0`, then checks `collateral >= borrowAmount`. For first-time borrowers this always passes, yet the function still executes a real borrow and transfers underlying.","impact":"Any account can open an initial borrow without sufficient collateral, creating immediate bad debt and enabling pool drain up to available liquidity.","paths":["CoreRouter.borrow -> getBorrowBalance.borrowIndex == 0 -> borrowAmount = 0 -> collateral check trivially passes -> LErc20.borrow(_amount) -> underlying transferred to borrower"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain borrow trusts stale source collateral snapshot (TOCTOU)","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:138","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:143","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:622"],"claim":"`borrowCrossChain` sends a one-time collateral snapshot (`payload.collateral`) from source chain, and destination execution validates only against this stale value instead of current source-chain collateral at execution time.","impact":"A borrower can initiate a cross-chain borrow, then reduce/remove collateral on the source chain before message execution, resulting in undercollateralized remote debt and protocol insolvency risk.","paths":["Chain A: borrowCrossChain captures collateral and sends message","Before destination execution: borrower redeems/withdraws source collateral","Chain B: _handleBorrowCrossChainRequest checks stale payload.collateral and executes borrow"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain debt is excluded from accounting due impossible EID condition","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:495","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:497","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:499","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:227"],"claim":"`LendStorage.borrowWithInterest` only counts `crossChainCollaterals` entries when both `destEid == currentEid` and `srcEid == currentEid`. Real cross-chain entries on destination chain have `srcEid != currentEid`, so they are skipped.","impact":"Borrow checks underestimate existing cross-chain debt (enabling repeated over-borrow), and cross-chain liquidation max-repay can collapse to zero, effectively preventing liquidation.","paths":["_handleBorrowCrossChainRequest -> getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral -> borrowWithInterest excludes existing cross-chain collateral debt -> new borrow allowed against understated debt","liquidateCrossChain -> getMaxLiquidationRepayAmount(false) -> borrowWithInterest returns 0 -> repayAmount check fails for real liquidations"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Source-chain cross-chain debt update drops accrued interest when refreshing borrow index","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:710","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:711","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:712"],"claim":"When an existing cross-chain borrow is updated in `_handleValidBorrowRequest`, principal is set to `oldPrinciple + payload.amount` and borrowIndex is overwritten with a newer index, without first normalizing old principal to the new index.","impact":"Repeated borrows can under-account true debt versus accrued debt, weakening solvency checks and reducing liquidation effectiveness.","paths":["Existing crossChainBorrows record at old borrowIndex","New ValidBorrowRequest arrives with higher payload.borrowIndex","Contract writes principle += amount and borrowIndex = payload.borrowIndex without accruing old principal"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Public cross-chain operations are protocol-fee sponsored, enabling native fee griefing","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:113","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:156","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:172","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:794","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:820"],"claim":"User-callable cross-chain functions trigger `_send`, which uses contract-native funds for LayerZero messaging (`_payNative` uses router balance and `_lzSend` is funded from contract balance) instead of caller-paid fees.","impact":"Attackers can spam cross-chain calls to burn router native balance and deny service for legitimate cross-chain operations until re-funded.","paths":["Attacker repeatedly calls borrowCrossChain / repayCrossChainBorrow / liquidateCrossChain","Each call sends LayerZero message funded by router-native balance","Router native reserve is depleted and later messages fail"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation finalization uses inconsistent token identity and impossible lookup parameters","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:355","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:361","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:445","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:448","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:452","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:479"],"claim":"`LiquidationSuccess/Failure` messages reuse `payload.destlToken` from the collateral chain, but receiving handlers treat it as a local token (`lTokenToUnderlying(payload.destlToken)`), and success lookup also hardcodes `destEid` to `0`. This causes mismatched lookups/reverts.","impact":"Cross-chain liquidation completion can fail deterministically, leaving cross-chain liquidation flow broken and creating unresolved debt/collateral state transitions or stuck message retries.","paths":["_handleLiquidationExecute sends LiquidationSuccess/LiquidationFailure with chain-A collateral lToken id","Receiver (_handleLiquidationSuccess/_handleLiquidationFailure) resolves local mappings using that id and/or destEid=0 lookup","findCrossChainCollateral/underlying resolution fails -> revert in finalization path"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation seizes collateral before repayment is enforced","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:312","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:330","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:355","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:443","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:464","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:483"],"claim":"`_handleLiquidationExecute` transfers collateral value from borrower to liquidator/protocol on the collateral chain before destination-chain repayment is collected. Repayment is only attempted later in `_handleLiquidationSuccess`, so failure there does not roll back the prior seize.","impact":"A liquidator can end up with seized collateral while debt repayment is not completed, causing borrower loss and protocol bad debt/state inconsistency.","paths":["Chain B: liquidateCrossChain sends CrossChainLiquidationExecute","Chain A: _handleLiquidationExecute immediately updates borrower/liquidator balances and sends LiquidationSuccess","Chain B: _handleLiquidationSuccess -> repayCrossChainBorrowInternal -> CoreRouter.repayCrossChainLiquidation may revert (e.g., missing allowance/balance)","Seizure already happened on chain A and remains while repayment is unfulfilled"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Supply accounting over-credits deposits using pre-mint exchange rate","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:74","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:77","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:80","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:87"],"claim":"`supply` computes credited lTokens from `exchangeRateStored()` before calling `mint()`. Since `mint()` can accrue interest and mint at a higher exchange rate, internal `mintTokens` credit can exceed actual lTokens received.","impact":"Users can be credited with more internal investment than the protocol actually minted, enabling value extraction at others’ expense and potential insolvency.","paths":["supply -> read exchangeRateStored (stale) -> mint accrues interest/updates rate -> actual minted lTokens < internal mintTokens -> inflated totalInvestment"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Same-chain liquidation shortfall check re-applies index growth to already-accrued borrow value","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:238","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:347","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:350"],"claim":"`liquidateBorrow` passes `borrowed` from `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`, which already includes accrued borrow effects; `liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal` multiplies by `currentBorrowIndex / storedBorrowIndex` again, overstating debt in the shortfall test.","impact":"Accounts can be treated as undercollateralized earlier than intended, enabling premature/unfair liquidation.","paths":["liquidateBorrow -> getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral returns borrowed/collateral","liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal computes borrowedAmount = borrowed * currentIndex / borrowBalance.borrowIndex","borrowedAmount becomes inflated -> `borrowedAmount > collateral` may pass for positions that should not be liquidatable"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain borrow aggregation can hard-revert when both direction records coexist","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:83","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:84","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:485","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:641","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:718"],"claim":"`borrowWithInterest` reverts if both `crossChainBorrows` and `crossChainCollaterals` are non-empty for a user/token. Opposite-direction cross-chain borrowing for the same underlying can populate both arrays on one chain, violating this assumption.","impact":"Borrow/liquidity/liquidation/repay flows that depend on borrow aggregation can revert, creating permissionless DoS and potentially locking user positions.","paths":["Direction A->B borrow creates `crossChainBorrows` on chain A for token X","Direction B->A borrow creates `crossChainCollaterals` on chain A for token X","Any call path invoking borrowWithInterest for that user/token reverts with invariant violation"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Unchecked ERC20 `transfer` can update protocol state without actual token payout","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:204"],"claim":"Payout paths use raw `IERC20.transfer` and ignore its boolean return value. For non-standard ERC20s that return `false` instead of reverting, execution continues and state changes persist despite failed transfer.","impact":"Users can be debited/indebted without receiving tokens, and protocol accounting can diverge from real token balances.","paths":["redeem/borrow/borrowForCrossChain performs stateful actions and calls raw transfer","token returns false (no revert)","function continues, leaving accounting changed but payout not delivered"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain repay lookup is ambiguous and keyed only by srcEid","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:397","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:406","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:539"],"claim":"`_getBorrowDetails` selects a collateral position using only `srcEid` within `crossChainCollaterals[borrower][underlying]`. If multiple positions share the same source chain but differ by other identifiers (e.g., source token), repayment can update the wrong position.","impact":"Repayments can be misattributed, corrupting debt records and impairing liquidation/accounting correctness.","paths":["Borrower has multiple cross-chain collateral records for same borrowed underlying with identical srcEid","repayCrossChainBorrow -> _getBorrowDetails picks first srcEid match","_updateRepaymentState and DestRepay message mutate/propagate wrong position data"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain liquidation health check uses seize amount as synthetic new borrow","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:273","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:276","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:431","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:433"],"claim":"When validating liquidation on the collateral chain, `_checkLiquidationValid` calls `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` with `borrowAmount = payload.amount`, but `payload.amount` is seizeTokens (collateral quantity), not pending debt. This distorts shortfall evaluation.","impact":"Liquidation eligibility can be misclassified, enabling liquidation of positions that are not actually underwater or causing inconsistent liquidation behavior.","paths":["Chain B computes seizeTokens and sends CrossChainLiquidationExecute with payload.amount = seizeTokens","Chain A _checkLiquidationValid treats payload.amount as hypothetical additional borrow","Borrowed-vs-collateral comparison is based on a wrong variable and can return true for otherwise healthy accounts"],"round":2,"source_agents":["merge_layer"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Missing reentrancy guards on critical entry points","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Generic missing-guard observation without a concrete reentrant path to protocol-level fund loss; ERC20 calls shown do not by themselves demonstrate exploitable reentrancy here."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation validation can be front-run on destination chain","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is normal liquidation competition behavior, not a protocol integrity bug; no